Sent: Sunday, January 08, 2012 5:44 PM
To: Paul Cohen
Cc: REST-Discuss Discussion Group
Subject: Re: [rest-discuss] The &quot;new media types are evil&quot; meme



On Sun, Jan 8, 2012 at 9:38 AM, Markus Lanthaler &lt;
&lt;mailto:markus.lanthaler@...&gt; markus.lanthaler@...&gt; wrote:



Paul Cohen wrote:
&gt; Having said that, I would be satisifed with one single new media type;
&gt; one that combines JSON:s simple expressiveness with native support for
&gt; hyperlinks! :-)

Have you had a look at JSON-LD? It offers much more than just support for
hyperlinks but you could &quot;abuse&quot; it just for getting that:
http://www.json-ld.org/spec/latest/json-ld-syntax/

Hi Paul,



If you only need links and embedding then HAL is much less convoluted than
JSON-LD:



http://blog.stateless.co/post/13296666138/json-linking-with-hal



Cheers,

Mike


